    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nPure python mode does not support memoryviews.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nConsider following code snippets:\r\n\r\n* cython\r\n```cython\r\nfrom cpython.array cimport array\r\ncdef array a = array('i', [1, 2, 3])\r\ncdef int[:] ca = a\r\n\r\nprint(ca[0])\r\n```\r\n\r\n* pure python\r\n```python\r\nimport cython\r\nfrom cython.cimports.cpython.array import array\r\na: array = array('i', [1, 2, 3])\r\nca: int[:] = a\r\n\r\nprint(ca[0])\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe snippets generates following C code:\r\n\r\n* cython\r\n```\r\n+4: cdef int[:] ca = a\r\n  __pyx_t_4 = __Pyx_PyObject_to_MemoryviewSlice_ds_int(((PyObject *)__pyx_v_10safe_usage_a), PyBUF_WRITABLE); if (unlikely(!__pyx_t_4.memview)) __PYX_ERR(0, 4, __pyx_L1_error)\r\n  __PYX_XCLEAR_MEMVIEW(&__pyx_v_10safe_usage_ca, 1);\r\n  __pyx_v_10safe_usage_ca = __pyx_t_4;\r\n  __pyx_t_4.memview = NULL;\r\n  __pyx_t_4.data = NULL;\r\n```\r\n\r\n* pure python\r\n\r\n```\r\n+4: ca: int[:] = a\r\n  __Pyx_GetModuleGlobalName(__pyx_t_2, __pyx_n_s_a); if (unlikely(!__pyx_t_2)) __PYX_ERR(0, 4, __pyx_L1_error)\r\n  __Pyx_GOTREF(__pyx_t_2);\r\n  if (PyDict_SetItem(__pyx_d, __pyx_n_s_ca, __pyx_t_2) < 0) __PYX_ERR(0, 4, __pyx_L1_error)\r\n  __Pyx_DECREF(__pyx_t_2); __pyx_t_2 = 0;\r\n```\r\n\r\nCython version correctly uses memoryview, but pure python just create assignment. \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nPure python mode should create memoryview as Cython language.\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: macOS\r\n - Python version: Python 3.9.7\r\n - Cython version: Master",
